Activity center models

Cara

2023-01-27

– Models with any spotted owl detection as response variable

1. effect of reproductive state

  any.repro.glm <- glm(cbind(Yes, No) ~ reproState, data = anyStocBern, family = binomial)

    tidy(any.repro.glm)
## # A tibble: 3 x 5
##   term              estimate std.error statistic p.value
##   <chr>                <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept)         -1.02      0.389    -2.63  0.00858
## 2 reproStatenest      -0.434     0.572    -0.758 0.448  
## 3 reproStatefledged    0.582     0.456     1.28  0.201
  #back-transformed coefficients (probabilities of detecting a spotted owl)
  allEffects(any.repro.glm)  
##  model: cbind(Yes, No) ~ reproState
## 
##  reproState effect
## reproState
##      pair      nest   fledged 
## 0.2647059 0.1891892 0.3918919

reorder levels so intercept is ‘fledged’

  anyStocBern2 <- anyStocBern
  anyStocBern2$reproState <- factor(anyStocBern2$reproState, levels = c('fledged','nest','pair'))  

  any.repro.glm.2 <- glm(cbind(Yes, No) ~ reproState, data = anyStocBern2, family = binomial)
  
    tidy(any.repro.glm.2)
